<br>
I'd suggest some new AA skills to raise the manna efficiency of our Nukes.<br>
<br>
Wildfire<br>
59 AA<br>
Turns all Wizard Fire based nukes into DoTs. The DD portion stays the same, but it does the entire damage of the DD again over 5 ticks (eg: Garrison's Superiour Sundering: 2100 DD, 420 Dmg/tick for 5 ticks.) at no additional save, so if we land even 1hp of the primary nuke, we still get our manna's worth in damage and if the nuke lands for full, woohoo! 100% manna efficiency increase. But at 420 dmg/tick I doubt it would really over-aggro us. NB. I don't think that multiple fire-based spells should be able to stack the DoT effect and why would you? Keep to the most efficient spell!<br>
<br>
And of course, one for cold too..<br>
<br>
Icicle Formation<br>
59 AA<br>
This turns all ice spells into a similar version of Elnerick's Entombment of Ice, but a Slow effect of 30% instead of a Root and a minor DoT for 50% the nuke's capacity over 5 ticks. (EG. Ice Comet: 1200 DD, 30% slow, DoT for 120/tick for 5 ticks) This again increases our manna efficiency but adds an additional effect which would benefit us in exp groups and raids on mobs who the shamen/encs would not bother slowing.<br>
<br>
This only effects Fire/Cold spells the way out Inherant Level 35+ ability allows us to land these types more efficiently.<br>
<br>
Of course, this has little to do with lower end Wizards, but I had a brain-fart last night and decided to put it out there.<br>
<br>
Questions? Comments? CONSTRUCTIVE criticisms??? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=milaru>Milaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Don't mind me,<BR>it's the PMS talking!</span><br>  Posts: 3526<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/02 9:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New AA skill to turn our DDs into DoTs</span><hr size=1> make a shaman or a necro if you want to dot things, we don't dot things.  <br>
<br>
It goes against the make thing dead now of the class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/02 3:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I loathe DoTs</span><hr size=1> One of the reasons I prioritise my Wizard/Magician characters is because I hate DoTs. It's no fun waiting for things to happen to take their full effect.<br>
<br>
With my idea, we don't wait for the full effect, we just get an extra bonus.<br>
<br>
Although I haven't crunched the numbers, I doubt doing double the damage for the same amount of manna would encroach on the SHM/NEC territory at all, but give us a bigger bang for our buck. Even if we were chain-nuking, 6 seconds usually elapse between landing each spell, so we'd get a biut of free damage out of it even if we re-applied.<br>
<br>
As everyone knows, we sacrifice manna efficiency for the greatest amount of damage in the shortest amount of time, but this only comes into full use when disaster strikes. My idea doesn't subtract from this fact of the Wiz class at all, but just adds to our overall manna efficiency. Would anyone really get all pissy even if we did get this AA? Magician get the Maelstrom line (which stack). This is basically the same theory.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying let's become Good Necros, I'm saying let's give ourselves better manna efficiency. Of course, I coudl just suggest lowering the cost of DD spells, but that requires little imagination. From a RP perspective, if you hit somoene with fire, they should catch alight and if you hit someone with ice, they should get bloody cold. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubriljin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Briljin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 8:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I loathe DoTs</span><hr size=1> Terrible idea for so many reasons but the biggest is there is a problem with stacking the same DoT, thus you would have the very same problem with you DD/DoT hyrbrid idea.  Not to mention there is already so few slots for active effects that the very last thing we need is another group of spells to take up more.<br>
<br>
Wizards are a DD class, be thankfull for that.<br>
<br>
Bril <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiwanthewicca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IwanTheWicca</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/02 2:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Elaborate</span><hr size=1> Okay, from a technical standpoint, the idea could not really be implimented. I'm not a guru on the exact mechanics of the EQ engine.<br>
<br>
But woudl you care to elaborate on the other reasons why my idea is &quot;terrible&quot;, Briljin?<br>
<br>
And as I said, the same element based spells would not stack, as in inferno shock would overwrite flame shock. It's not that hard of a thing to. The onyl 2 effects that Wizards could stack wodul be an ice and fire based spell and that is all. Also when the same dot is cast upon the mob, it doesn't stack with itself, it just renews the duration.<br>
<br>
Also I was proposing it as an AA skill, not a retroactive change to all spells. Those of you who are DD fanatics would be free to not use this AA and those of us who would, can.<br>
<br>
Please excuse me if I seem hostile but I fail to see how this is such a bad idea. it's all very well making sweeping statements with nothing to back it up, but it doesn't explain the &quot;WHY&quot;! if it's just ebcause you don't like the idea, then fine. But can't you see the merits of it? Engine schmengine! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 7940<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/02 2:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elaborate</span><hr size=1> It sounds to me like you want DDs to be more like rains. How about an AA that lowers the resists of rains? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-photo-short.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a>
<br>
<font size=1></font><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41790" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/bottom.gif" height=12 width=239 alt="an enthralled  says 'Uoy ekil semong etah yllaeri!'" border=0 vspace=5></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/5/02 9:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elaborate</span><hr size=1> Why is this a terrible idea?<br>
<br>
Dots are NOT a wizard thing.<br>
<br>
Your best Dot dmg per tick would be almost double the dmg of the best necro or shaman dots.<br>
<br>
The increased dmg would be overpowering.<br>
<br>
Pvp would become more of a joke than it allready is.<br>
<br>
This is the most ridiculous idea I've heard since the post on the safehouse suggesting casters be given the ability to cast on the run like bards. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubriljin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Briljin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/5/02 11:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elaborate</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
But woudl you care to elaborate on the other reasons why my idea is &quot;terrible&quot;, Briljin?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I take it you are not familiar with DoTs?  Just a quick run down for you.<br>
<br>
1) Unlike DD DoTs do not work with the AA Fury skill<br>
2) Because DoTs have an active affect upon the mob only one instance of any one DoT maybe active at once.  Thus even if you have 4 Necromancers with Funeral Prye, only one Funeral Pyre will be active at any given time.<br>
3) Currently there can only be 15 active effects upon a mob at one time.  If there is not room for the new effect or it does not over write a currently active effect then it does not take hold (ie does no damage) and STILL costs you mana.<br>
<br>
Currently Wizards have just about the best means of delivering magical damage (due to the above limitations).  Trust me you do not want to change that, hell I end up using DD just as often as DoTs upon raids for the above reason...<br>
<br>
DoTs look great upon paper, it is not until you actually use them that their flaws become apparent.<br>
<br>
Bril <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwizardizzara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wizard Izzara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/8/02 7:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elaborate</span><hr size=1> I am quite against this idea. First of, like many have said, wizards do DD, not DoT's or any other crap. Then the idea of an AA increasing your damage output by 100%? wow. just wow, im sure no one would have a problem with that. If somehow that were to happen, might aswell just make it so all DD's take 1/2 mana cost, or twice the damage (very likely). Im sure no one would mind wizards running around with 8:1 ratio on ice spear /snicker <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
